NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|It is almost never right to play in 5 of a minor vs. 3N, unless you are sure the opponents can run a suit. That is a very important bidding principle. If you think 3N has plays, bid it rather than 5 of a minor.|
