^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|A good rule of thumb is that on competitive hands, if you have a spade fit and they have a heart fit 4S is almost always right over 4H. Stan knows they have a heart fit, as it is very unlikely, once I bid a weak 2, that I have more than 2 or 3 hearts so he should bid 4S. It is possible that both 4H and 4S are going down. But it is more likely that it will be to our advantage. |
PG| ***** 51 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|We might be making 4S. They might be making 4H. Or they might bid 5H over 4S and go down 1. So with most experts 4S is almost automatic over 4H. Many people worry about what could go wrong when they make a bid. A better way to look at it is to see if it is likely that something good will happen when you bid. If the odds favor something good happening, then make the bid.|
