^-{            When to Sacrifice -from a mentoring session many years ago         }
^-|
fp||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let me discuss when it is good to sacrifice, and when not. For the sake of this discussion, assume the  opponents have bid a makable major suit game, and they are going to double your sacrifice.|
PG| ***** 127 ***** |


AT|

At equal vulnerability, assuming the opponents make game, down 2 is a good sacrifice, down 3 is not. For example, non-vulnerable, down 2 is minus 300, and game is 420. And if we are both vulnerable, down 2 is minus 500, and they are plus 620. Down 3, not vulnerable, is not terrible, 500 vs. 420. On the other hand, down 3 vulnerable is not good, 800 vs. 620.|
PG| ***** 128 ***** |


AT|

If you are not vulnerable and they are vulnerable, it is ok to go down 3, 500 vs. 620.|
PG| ***** 129 ***** |


AT|

If you are vul and the opponents are not, it is almost never right to sacrifice. They have to be making the hand, and you can only be down 1 (200 vs. 420).|
PG| ***** 130 ***** |


AT|

In summary, the best time to sacrifice is when you are not vulnerable and they are. I would also occasionally consider a sacrifice if both are not vulnerable, particularly if you think there is a chance that you might even make the contract (for example, when both sides have fits in 2 suits). However it is rarely right to sacrifice when you are vulnerable, even if the opponents are also vulnerable.
|
PG| ***** 131 ***** |


AT|

^B@2^*BMM: ^*NThe above section is from a mentoring session in 2007.|
